\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 Be merciful to me a sinn\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 er, bereft of every good deed, raise up my fallen soul which hath become defiled by countless sins, and take away from me every evil thought of this visible life. 
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 Forgive my sins, O Only Sinless One, in which I have sinned against Thee this day, known or \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 unknown, in word, and deed, and thought and in all my senses. 
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 Do Thou Thyself protect and guard me from every opposing circumstance, by Thy Divine authority and power and inexpressible love for mankind. 
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 Blot out, O God, blot out the multitude of my sins.\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 
 Be pleased, O Lord, to deliver me from the net of the Evil One, and save my passionate soul, and overshadow me with the light of Thy countenance when Thou shalt come in glory; and cause me, uncondemned now, to sleep a dreamless sleep, and keep Thy servan
\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 t\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  untroubled by thoughts, and drive away from me all satanic deeds; and enlighten for me the eyes of my heart with understanding, lest I sleep unto death. 
